-- Japan's Sharp to become Pioneer's top shareholder
-- 
-- Thu Sep 20, 2007 4:17am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/20/us-sharp-pioneer-alliance-idUSTKV00288720070920

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Struggling consumer electronics maker Pioneer Corp ( 6773.T ) said it would raise 41.4 billion yen ($357 million) by issuing new shares to Sharp Corp ( 6753.T ), making Sharp its top shareholder with a 14.3 percent stake. 

 Pioneer said it would issue 30 million shares to Sharp, while Sharp said it would allot 10 million of its existing shares to Pioneer. Sharp is one of the world's top makers of liquid crystal display (LCD) TVs, while Pioneer is a producer of plasma display televisions, audio equipment and car electronics.